

Emacs desktops save/restore the list of open files. They can do this on a per-
sandbox basis if you add something like this to your .emacs files. Usually
requires "M-x desktop-save" once in each sandbox to start auto save/restore.


(setq desktop-dirname "~"
      desktop-base-file-name (concat ".emacs.desktop." (getenv "SANDBOX"))
      desktop-base-lock-name (concat desktop-base-file-name ".lock")
      desktop-load-locked-desktop nil
      desktop-save 'if-exists)
(desktop-save-mode 1)
